.TH NAMEFIX 1 "July 2026" "namefix 1.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
namefix \- cross-platform filename validator and sanitizer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B namefix
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B namefix
validates and sanitizes filenames to ensure compatibility across Windows, Linux, macOS, and Android.
It detects reserved names, forbidden characters, and other filesystem issues that could cause problems
when sharing files between different operating systems.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-check
Check mode (default). Detect problems without making changes.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-fix
Fix mode. Sanitize problematic filenames.
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-undo
Undo mode. Restore original filenames from backup.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dry\-run
Preview changes without applying them.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Prompt for confirmation before each rename.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-batch
Apply fixes automatically without prompting.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Process subdirectories recursively.
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-json
Output results in JSON format.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show detailed output.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-strategy " " \fISTRATEGY\fR
Sanitization strategy: \fBunderscore\fR (default), \fBhyphen\fR, or \fBremove\fR.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information.
.SH DETECTED ISSUES
.TP
.B Forbidden characters
Characters not allowed on Windows: < > : " | ? * \\ /
.TP
.B Control characters
ASCII control characters (0-31) and DEL (127).
.TP
.B Reserved names
Windows reserved device names: CON, PRN, AUX, NUL, COM1-9, LPT1-9.
.TP
.B Trailing dots/spaces
Filenames ending with dots or spaces (problematic on Windows).
.TP
.B Leading spaces
Filenames starting with spaces.
.TP
.B Length exceeded
Filenames exceeding 255 bytes.
.TP
.B Problematic Unicode
Zero-width characters, RTL marks, and certain emoji ranges.
.TP
.B Case conflicts
Multiple files that differ only in case (problematic on case-insensitive systems).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success, no problems found (check mode) or all fixes applied.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred during operation.
.TP
.B 2
Problems detected (check mode only).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .namefix_backup/
Directory containing backup information for undo functionality.
.TP
.I .namefix_undo.log
Log file recording original and new filenames.
.SH EXAMPLES
Check current directory for issues:
.RS
.B namefix .
.RE
.PP
Preview fixes without applying:
.RS
.B namefix \-f \-d ~/Downloads
.RE
.PP
Interactive fix mode:
.RS
.B namefix \-f \-i /path/to/files
.RE
.PP
Batch fix recursively:
.RS
.B namefix \-f \-b \-r /path/to/files
.RE
.PP
Undo previous renames:
.RS
.B namefix \-u .
.RE
.PP
JSON output for scripting:
.RS
.B namefix \-c \-j . > report.json
.RE
